{"id":44,"ayahs":[{"number":260,"arabic":"وَإِذْ قَالَ إِبْرَٰهِۦمُ رَبِّ أَرِنِى كَيْفَ تُحْىِ ٱلْمَوْتَىٰ ۖ قَالَ أَوَلَمْ تُؤْمِن ۖ قَالَ بَلَىٰ وَلَٰكِن لِّيَطْمَئِنَّ قَلْبِى ۖ قَالَ فَخُذْ أَرْبَعَةًۭ مِّنَ ٱلطَّيْرِ فَصُرْهُنَّ إِلَيْكَ ثُمَّ ٱجْعَلْ عَلَىٰ كُلِّ جَبَلٍۢ مِّنْهُنَّ جُزْءًۭا ثُمَّ ٱدْعُهُنَّ يَأْتِينَكَ سَعْيًۭا ۚ وَٱعْلَمْ أَنَّ ٱللَّهَ عَزِيزٌ حَكِيمٌۭ","translation":"And, lo, Abraham said: \"O my Sustainer! Show me how Thou givest life unto the dead!\" Said He: \"Hast thou, then, no faith?\" (Abraham) answered: \"Yea, but [let me see it] so that my heart may be set fully at rest.\" Said He: \"Take, then, four birds and teach them to obey thee; then place them separately on every hill [around thee]; then summon them: they will come flying to thee. And know that God is almighty, wise.\"","audio":"https://cdn.islamic.network/quran/audio/128/ar.alafasy/267.mp3","surahId":2,"words":[{"id":87384,"position":1,"arabic":"وَإِذْ","translation":"এবং যখন","audioUrl":"wbw/002_260_001.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":87385,"position":2,"arabic":"قَالَ","translation":"বলল","audioUrl":"wbw/002_260_002.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":87386,"position":3,"arabic":"إِبْرَٰهِـۧمُ","translation":"ইবরাহীম","audioUrl":"wbw/002_260_003.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":87387,"position":4,"arabic":"رَبِّ","translation":"হে আমার রব","audioUrl":"wbw/002_260_004.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":87388,"position":5,"arabic":"أَرِنِى","translation":"দেখাও আমাকে","audioUrl":"wbw/002_260_005.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":87389,"position":6,"arabic":"كَيْفَ","translation":"কীভাবে","audioUrl":"wbw/002_260_006.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":87390,"position":7,"arabic":"تُحْىِ","translation":"তুমি জীবিত কর","audioUrl":"wbw/002_260_007.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":87391,"position":8,"arabic":"ٱلْمَوْتَىٰ ۖ","translation":"মৃতদেরকে","audioUrl":"wbw/002_260_008.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":87393,"position":9,"arabic":"قَالَ","translation":"তিনি বললেন","audioUr